Executive Profile
Robin W. T. Buchanan  Senior Adviser, Bain & Company, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships65--
Background

		Mr. Robin W. T. Buchanan, also known as Rob, serves as the Senior Adviser of Bain & Company Inc. Mr. Buchanan joined Bain & Company in 1982 and has been involved in strategy development and organization advice for its clients in most industry sectors, including healthcare. Prior to Mr. Buchanan's career with Bain & Company, he served at American Express International Banking Corporation in New York, McKinsey & Company and Deloitte & Touche, where he qualified as a Chartered ... Accountant. He was a Principal at Standard Chartered International (USA) Ltd. He served as Managing Partner Senior Partner of Bain in the UK from 1990 to 2007. From 2007 to 2009, he was employed at The Institute of Chartered Accountants in England & Wales. Mr. Buchanan served as Dean and then President of London Business School. Mr. Buchanan served as the Chairman of Michael Page International plc from December 31, 2011 to December 31, 2015. He has been an Independent Non-Executive Director at Schroders Plc since March 4, 2010. He is a Member of the Trilateral Commission, of the Advisory Board of the UK India Business Council and of the International Advisory Council of Recipco. He has been a Member of Supervisory Board at LyondellBasell Industries N.V. since May 10, 2011. He served as a Director of Michael Page International plc from August 10, 2011 to December 31, 2015. He served as a Non-Executive Director of Liberty International PLC (now Capital Shopping Centres Group PLC) from June 1997 to December 2008. He served as a Non Executive Director of Shire Limited from July 30, 2003 to July 29, 2008. Mr. Buchanan holds an M.B.A. from 1977 to 1979 with Baker Scholar (distinction) from Harvard Business School.Read Full Background




